HEADWORD: Amphiuma
<hw>Am`phi*u"ma</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧m`f⟦icr⟧*⟦umac⟧"m⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of amphibians, inhabiting
the Southern United States, having a serpentlike form, but with four
minute limbs and two persistent gill openings; the Congo
snake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

